# Accessibility Standards (WCAG 2.1 AA)

This document defines accessibility requirements for all web application features. Every UI component and page must meet WCAG 2.1 AA compliance.

---

## Color and Contrast

### Minimum Contrast Ratios

| Element | Minimum Ratio | Tool to Verify |
|---------|---------------|----------------|
| Normal text (< 18px) | 4.5:1 | Chrome DevTools, axe |
| Large text (>= 18px or >= 14px bold) | 3:1 | Chrome DevTools, axe |
| UI components and graphical objects | 3:1 | Manual check |
| Focus indicators | 3:1 against adjacent colors | Manual check |

### Color Independence

- [ ] Information conveyed by color is also conveyed by text, pattern, or icon
- [ ] Status indicators use icons in addition to color (green check, red X)
- [ ] Charts and graphs use patterns or labels, not just color differentiation
- [ ] Form validation errors use icons and text, not just red borders

```html
<!-- WRONG: Color only -->
<span style="color: red">Error</span>

<!-- RIGHT: Color + icon + text -->
<span class="error" role="alert">
  <svg aria-hidden="true"><!-- error icon --></svg>
  Error: Email address is required
</span>
```

