## Semantic HTML

### Document Structure

```html
<header>
  <nav aria-label="Main navigation">...</nav>
</header>
<main>
  <h1>Page Title</h1>
  <section aria-labelledby="section-heading">
    <h2 id="section-heading">Section</h2>
  </section>
</main>
<footer>...</footer>
```

### Heading Hierarchy

- [ ] Every page has exactly one `h1`
- [ ] Headings are nested sequentially (h1 -> h2 -> h3, no skipping)
- [ ] Headings describe the content that follows
- [ ] Headings are not used for visual styling alone

### Landmark Roles

| HTML Element | Implicit Role | Required |
|-------------|---------------|----------|
| `<header>` | banner | Yes |
| `<nav>` | navigation | Yes |
| `<main>` | main | Yes |
| `<footer>` | contentinfo | Yes |
| `<aside>` | complementary | When applicable |

---

## ARIA Usage

### Rules of ARIA

1. **Prefer native HTML** -- use `<button>`, not `<div role="button">`
2. **Do not change native semantics** -- do not add `role="heading"` to `<button>`
3. **All ARIA controls must be keyboard accessible**
4. **Do not use `role="presentation"` or `aria-hidden="true"` on focusable elements**
5. **All interactive elements must have accessible names**

### Common Patterns

```html
<!-- Live region for dynamic updates -->
<div aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true">
  Results updated: 42 items found
</div>

<!-- Loading state -->
<div aria-busy="true" aria-live="polite">
  Loading results...
</div>

<!-- Expandable section -->
<button aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="details-panel">
  Show Details
</button>
<div id="details-panel" hidden>...</div>
```

