## Forms

### Labels and Instructions

- [ ] Every form input has a visible `<label>` element
- [ ] Labels are associated via `for`/`id` or wrapping
- [ ] Required fields are indicated (not just with asterisk)
- [ ] Instructions are provided before the form, not just in tooltips

### Error Handling

- [ ] Errors are announced to screen readers via `aria-live` or `role="alert"`
- [ ] Error messages are adjacent to the field they reference
- [ ] Error messages describe how to fix the issue
- [ ] Focus moves to the first error on form submission

```html
<label for="email">Email (required)</label>
<input id="email" type="email" aria-describedby="email-error" aria-invalid="true" />
<p id="email-error" role="alert">Please enter a valid email address</p>
```

---

## Images and Media

- [ ] Decorative images use `alt=""` or `aria-hidden="true"`
- [ ] Informative images have descriptive alt text
- [ ] Complex images (charts, diagrams) have long descriptions
- [ ] Videos have captions and transcripts

---

## Testing Checklist

### Automated Testing

```bash
# axe-core in CI
npx axe-cli http://localhost:3000 --exit

# Lighthouse accessibility audit
npx lighthouse http://localhost:3000 --only-categories=accessibility
```

### Manual Testing

- [ ] Navigate entire page using only keyboard
- [ ] Test with screen reader (VoiceOver, NVDA, JAWS)
- [ ] Test with browser zoom at 200%
- [ ] Test with high-contrast mode
- [ ] Verify focus order matches visual order
